Typealiases.html#/s:19SudoPasswordManage.name: VaultItemNote
Typealiases.html#/s:19SudoPasswordManage.abstract: Represents a note for items in the vault. Maintains backwards compatibility.

Structs/PasswordManagerError/ErrorType.h.name: versionMismatch
Structs/PasswordManagerError/ErrorType.h.abstract: The version of the vault that’s being updated or deleted does not match the version stored in the backed. It is likely that another client updated the vault first so the caller should reconcile the changes before attempting to update or delete the vault.

Structs/PasswordManagerError/ErrorType.h.name: notAuthorized
Structs/PasswordManagerError/ErrorType.h.abstract: The user is not authorized to perform the requested operation. This maybe due to specifying the wrong key deriving key or password.

Structs/PasswordManagerError/ErrorType.h.name: invalidVault
Structs/PasswordManagerError/ErrorType.h.abstract: The vault data retrieved is invalid. This indicates the vault is corrupt or is encrypted using a key that’s not known to the client.

Structs/PasswordManagerError/ErrorType.h.name: vaultLocked
Structs/PasswordManagerError/ErrorType.h.abstract: The vault is locked and must be unlocked before this action will succeed.

Structs/PasswordManagerError/ErrorType.h.name: invalidPasswordOrMissingSecretCode
Structs/PasswordManagerError/ErrorType.h.abstract: The password is invalid or no secret code exists locally.

Structs/PasswordManagerError/ErrorType.h.name: invalidFormat
Structs/PasswordManagerError/ErrorType.h.abstract: The format of the input was invalid.

Structs/PasswordManagerError/ErrorType.h.name: security
Structs/PasswordManagerError/ErrorType.h.abstract: There was a problem using Security framework, e.g. unable to access the keychain or generate secure keys.

Structs/PasswordManagerError/ErrorType.h.name: secureVaultService
Structs/PasswordManagerError/ErrorType.h.abstract: An error was returned by the Sudo Secure Vault service.

Structs/PasswordManagerError/ErrorType.h.name: internal
Structs/PasswordManagerError/ErrorType.h.abstract: An internal error occured. This is most likely due to an internal framework, e.g unable to generate encryption keys.

Structs/PasswordManagerError/ErrorType.h.name: asError()
Structs/PasswordManagerError/ErrorType.h.abstract: Converts the error type into an error

Structs/PasswordManagerError/ErrorType.h.name: ErrorType
Structs/PasswordManagerError/ErrorType.h.abstract: Types of the errors returned by the password manager.

Structs/PasswordManagerError.html#/s:19S.name: underlyingError
Structs/PasswordManagerError.html#/s:19S.abstract: A reference to the underlying error which caused this, if it exists.

Structs/PasswordManagerError.html#/s:19S.name: userInfo
Structs/PasswordManagerError.html#/s:19S.abstract: An optional place to put additional error related information.

Structs/EntitlementState.html#/s:19SudoP.name: sudoId
Structs/EntitlementState.html#/s:19SudoP.abstract: Sudo which owns the entitlement consuming vaults

Structs/Entitlement/Name.html.name: Name
Structs/Entitlement/Name.html.abstract: Enum that represents the different type of entitlements available

Structs/Entitlement.html.name: Entitlement
Structs/Entitlement.html.abstract: Data to represent the entitlements for Password Manager

Structs/EntitlementState.html.name: EntitlementState
Structs/EntitlementState.html.abstract: Data to represent the current Entitlement State for Password Manager

Structs/PasswordManagerError.html.name: PasswordManagerError
Structs/PasswordManagerError.html.abstract: Wrapper for errors that are returned from the password manager.

Protocols/SudoPasswordManagerClient.html.name: getRegistrationStatus(completion:)
Protocols/SudoPasswordManagerClient.html.abstract: Checks if the password manager is registered.

Protocols/SudoPasswordManagerClient.html.name: register(masterPassword:completion:)
Protocols/SudoPasswordManagerClient.html.abstract: Registers with the service.

Protocols/SudoPasswordManagerClient.html.name: getSecretCode()
Protocols/SudoPasswordManagerClient.html.abstract: Returns the secret code needed to bootstrap a new device.

Protocols/SudoPasswordManagerClient.html.name: lock()
Protocols/SudoPasswordManagerClient.html.abstract: Locks the password manager.

Protocols/SudoPasswordManagerClient.html.name: unlock(masterPassword:secretCode:completion:)
Protocols/SudoPasswordManagerClient.html.abstract: Unlocks the password manager.

Protocols/SudoPasswordManagerClient.html.name: reset()
Protocols/SudoPasswordManagerClient.html.abstract: Removes all keys and any cached data associated with this client.

Protocols/SudoPasswordManagerClient.html.name: deregister(completion:)
Protocols/SudoPasswordManagerClient.html.abstract: Deregisters the vault user associated with this client.

Protocols/SudoPasswordManagerClient.html.name: isLocked()
Protocols/SudoPasswordManagerClient.html.abstract: Checks if the vault is locked or not

Protocols/SudoPasswordManagerClient.html.name: createVault(sudoId:completion:)
Protocols/SudoPasswordManagerClient.html.abstract: Creates a new vault on the service. Requires password manager to be registered and unlocked.

Protocols/SudoPasswordManagerClient.html.name: listVaults(completion:)
Protocols/SudoPasswordManagerClient.html.abstract: Fetches all vaults

Protocols/SudoPasswordManagerClient.html.name: getVault(withId:completion:)
Protocols/SudoPasswordManagerClient.html.abstract: Fetches the vault with the specifided id. Requires password manager to be registered and unlocked.

Protocols/SudoPasswordManagerClient.html.name: deleteVault(withId:completion:)
Protocols/SudoPasswordManagerClient.html.abstract: Deletes a vault. Does not require the password manager to be unlocked.

Protocols/SudoPasswordManagerClient.html.name: changeMasterPassword(currentPassword:newPassword:completion:)
Protocols/SudoPasswordManagerClient.html.abstract: Change the master password. Requires password manager to be registered and unlocked.

Protocols/SudoPasswordManagerClient.html.name: add(item:toVault:completion:)
Protocols/SudoPasswordManagerClient.html.abstract: Asynchronously adds a new item to the vault. Requires password manager to be registered and unlocked.

Protocols/SudoPasswordManagerClient.html.name: listVaultItems(inVault:completion:)
Protocols/SudoPasswordManagerClient.html.abstract: Asynchronously returns the full list of credentials stored in the vault. Requires password manager to be registered and unlocked.

Protocols/SudoPasswordManagerClient.html.name: getVaultItem(id:in:completion:)
Protocols/SudoPasswordManagerClient.html.abstract: Asynchronously returns a single item if the id can be found. Requires password manager to be registered and unlocked.

Protocols/SudoPasswordManagerClient.html.name: update(item:in:completion:)
Protocols/SudoPasswordManagerClient.html.abstract: Asynchronously updates a credential in the vault. Requires password manager to be registered and unlocked.

Protocols/SudoPasswordManagerClient.html.name: removeVaultItem(id:from:completion:)
Protocols/SudoPasswordManagerClient.html.abstract: Asynchronously removes the vault item with the specified id. Requires password manager to be registered and unlocked.

Protocols/SudoPasswordManagerClient.html.name: renderRescueKit()
Protocols/SudoPasswordManagerClient.html.abstract: Creates a Rescue Kit PDF with the user’s secret code using the default template.

Protocols/SudoPasswordManagerClient.html.name: renderRescueKit(templatePDF:)
Protocols/SudoPasswordManagerClient.html.abstract: Creates a Rescue Kit PDF with the user’s secret code from the provided template.

Protocols/SudoPasswordManagerClient.html.name: getEntitlement(completion:)
Protocols/SudoPasswordManagerClient.html.abstract: Fetches the list of [Entitlement] that indicates the resources the user is entitled to use.

Protocols/SudoPasswordManagerClient.html.name: getEntitlementState(completion:)
Protocols/SudoPasswordManagerClient.html.abstract: Fetches the current [EntitlementState] which includes information about how many entitlements have been consumed.

Protocols/SudoPasswordManagerClient.html.name: SudoPasswordManagerClient
Protocols/SudoPasswordManagerClient.html.abstract: Client to access password manager functionality.

Enums/PasswordManagerRegistrationStatus..name: registered
Enums/PasswordManagerRegistrationStatus..abstract: Returning user, known device. User can interact with vaults after unlocking with master password.

Enums/PasswordManagerRegistrationStatus..name: notRegistered
Enums/PasswordManagerRegistrationStatus..abstract: New User, new device. This is a first time user. User must choose a master password and register.

Enums/PasswordManagerRegistrationStatus..name: missingSecretCode
Enums/PasswordManagerRegistrationStatus..abstract: Returning user, new device. Password manager requires the secret code which was generated when they first registered.

Enums/SecureFieldValue.html.abstract: SecureField provider either provides a plain text value or cipher-text along with a function that decrypts it.
